lor=#A62A2A>(1/21/02 3:58:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=265.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Does anyone else tire of complaints about the ruleset?</span><hr size=1> I do understand that many dont like the ruleset..but Verant isnt going to change it....for it seems although one dont like it...another does.  So all the ranting and raving does nothing...unless your whole point is to just let off steam.<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=rexfelix>Rexfelix</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 59<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/21/02 4:07:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=265.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Does anyone else tire of complaints about the ruleset?</span><hr size=1> I think that's what most of it is about - better to vent here than to start honking your horn in traffic I figure. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=aradil>Aradil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 33<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/21/02 4:22:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=265.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Does anyone else tire of complaints about the ruleset?</span><hr size=1> I think sometimes people come here to vent about a problem with the ruleset, but then someone else posts and says they have found a way to cope with it that is as good as or even better than if the rules weren't there. So that's a good thing, at least. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=rexfelix>Rexfelix</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 61<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/21/02 5:06:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=265.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Does anyone else tire of complaints about the ruleset?</span><hr size=1> Aye Aradil, the whole concept of &quot;community&quot; is for people to express their likes and dislikes so that understanding and relationships can form.<br>
<br>
There has been some heated discussion on this board/server, but it is relatively healthy - compared to what you can find on many other servers/boards.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukzanverto.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kzan Verto</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 131<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/21/02 6:23:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=265.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Does anyone else tire of complaints about the ruleset?</span><hr size=1> Ya.<br>
 <p>Kzan Verto<BR>
Giver of "da juice" (tm)
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukarlithas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Karlithas</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalWhite.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 54<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/21/02 6:32:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=265.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Does anyone else tire of complaints about the ruleset?</span><hr size=1> i love complaints....if it's done right, it would inspire many interesting discussions.  Besides, no matter how heated the discussions were, the majority of the discussion is maintained at a civilized level.  That is one reason that I am proud that I am in this FV community.  So...no, I am not tired of complaints!  Keep 'em coming! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubjond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 250<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/22/02 1:01:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=265.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   I love arguing about the ..</span><hr size=1> .. ruleset.  It's pointless, but well, so is playing EQ and you get to know what everyone thinks and how they handle themselves.  It's the verbal equivalent of dropping small bombs into people's heads so you can use the echoes to map their interiors. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uroawen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Roawen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 38<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/22/02 1:28:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=265.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I love arguing about the ..</span><hr size=1> I am not a huge fan of all the &quot;complaining&quot; going on within these boards. That being said, I have two points to make.<br>
1) It is BY FAR better than all the other CRAP being posted on blue server boards. While there are posts that say nothing more than &quot;TLC sucks&quot; there are lots of replies saying &quot;I know how you feel, but let me know if you need help getting the piece you need&quot;<br>
and<br>
2) We have to remember how &quot;young&quot; this server really is. I has only been live for a few months. Given the fact that it is a &quot;start from scratch&quot; server, that is not a very long time... so we're all getting used to each other, and the idiosyncrasies of this server... <br>
so I think the &quot;complaining&quot; is actually very healthy and I am glad to see most everyone doing it in a beneficial way (rather than saying &quot;I hate this stupid rule, I quit!&quot;)<br>
<br>
In Perfect Hate, and Perfect Faith,<br>
Roawen <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uxsatyrx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>xsatyrx</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 92<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/23/02 5:44:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=265.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I love arguing about the ..</span><hr size=1> I agree with ya Roawen...guess the thing is the continual same rants that have been posted over and over and then a new thread on the EXACT same thing...over and over...and then a new thread on the EXACT same thing..over and over...and then...well you get the picture. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/urobingoodfellow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Robin Goodfellow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 97<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/24/02 4:31:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=265.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I love arguing about the ..</span><hr size=1> xsatyrx:<br>
<br>
I agree (but you knew that).  What grows wearisome to me are the attempts to persuade by using appeals to &quot;server death&quot;, and the predictions of doom before the server's really gotten a start.  Every complaint about the rules seems to follow the same pattern, which is &quot;If VI would get rid of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> x</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, then more people would come to the server&quot; or, alternately, &quot;I've heard from a lot of people (Nixon's 'Silent Majority', anyone?) that they'd come to Firiona Vie except for <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> x</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.&quot;<br>
<br>
If the complaining were a tad more honest, I might be persuaded.  If people said &quot;I wish they'd change the Trivial Loot Code because I'm having problems getting an item I desire&quot; or &quot;I wish they'd change the forced /roleplay because I'm having trouble finding groups&quot;, I feel people would be being more genuine in their rhetoric.<br>
<br>
Also, if VI were to capitulate to all the complaints, we'd have a blue server with the label &quot;Roleplaying Preferred&quot; (and maybe not even that, given the tone of last week's posts): there's a camp of people vehemently opposed to the forced /roleplay, there's a camp of people opposed to the TLC (although this camp, it seems, has two branches: the large &quot;Change it&quot; branch and the smaller &quot;It's totally broken, get rid of it&quot; branch), there's a camp of people who still oppose the language rules (/boggle), etc.<br>
<br>
Lasgalen <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukzanverto.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kzan Verto</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 158<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/25/02 4:39:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=265.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I love arguing about the ..</span><hr size=1> And then there are all those players that just use common sense...most of the time.<br>
 <p>Kzan Verto<BR>
Giver of "da juice" (tm)
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/utwotribes.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Twotribes</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Troll</span><br>  Posts: 212<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/26/02 12:44:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=265.topic&index=11>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Does anyone else tire of complaints about the ruleset?</span><hr size=1> Personally.....<br>
<br>
I find it annoying that people complain about people complaining. But then that is a personal opinion.<br>
<br>
I agree that a gazillion posts get started about the same complaint ( no matter which one it is) and that it can be a tad annoying to wade through the same old complaint when you pesonally dont agree with the complaint.<br>
<br>
But on the same note I find it BEYOND annoying when people post a position in opposition ( read complaint if you like) to a ruleset, provide ample examples of why they feel it is a problem, then get bombarded by the &quot;I love this rule&quot; crowd. Usually (not always I agree) along the lines of taking the listed complaints out of text to explain why they arent a problem. Usually meaning &quot;it doesnt effect me so NAH&quot;.<br>
<br>
If you disagree, post why you think it is appropriate, with personal reasons why you think so.<br>
<br>
Attacking a post with &quot; stop complain&quot; is a waste of everyones time. For one thing, NOTHING will get changed if NO one ever complains. Not saying that any thing will get changed and not saying my opinion is any more important than anyone elses (well except to me). It would be far more productive to respond with a statement along the lines of &quot; I dont see a need to change the rule set&quot;.<br>
<br>
There are legitimate reasons to question rulesets in any situation.... unless of course you subscribe to the theory that someone is perfect. DO those reasons rise to the level of requiring  a serious look at MAKING a change? Well we would never know if everyone simply didnt question, now would we? And I understand that this board and its posters are in no real position to make any changes. BUT Verant can and will (usually after it being force feed down their throats) make changes based on HEAVY player input. And history shows us that it usually takes down right threats with real consequences to get Verant to listen to the most reasonable requests for even LOOKING at a request for change.<br>
<br>
